      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "#93381: Expose tool_use blocks in llm_output / agent_end hook payloads",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nExpose tool-use content blocks (`tool_use`) in the `llm_output` and `agent_end` hook event payloads via a new `toolUses` field. Each entry carries the tool `name` + `input`, enabling downstream supervisor plugins to enforce per-bot tool-level policy deterministically from the hook, rather than inferring tool invocations from prose.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #93381\n\n- Hook payloads for conversation-access hooks (`agent_end` / `llm_output`) previously only delivered the assistant's text output (`assistantTexts`) but not the structured `tool_use` content blocks. This forced supervisors to parse raw `lastAssistant` message content or rely on text-heuristic guessing.\n- Companion to #92783 (scheduled-action force-run / dry-run) — same downstream-supervisor consumer, different missing signal.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`PluginHookLlmOutputEvent.assistantTexts` only collects text content blocks (`type === \"text\"`) from the assistant message. The `tool_use` blocks (tool `name` + `input`) present in the underlying assistant message content array were not collected into any explicit, type-safe field in the hook event payload.\n\nThe raw data existed in `lastAssistant` (typed as `unknown`) and in `agent_end.messages`, but required unsafe casting and manual content-block parsing to extract.\n\n**Files affected:**\n- `src/plugins/hook-types.ts` — event type definitions\n- `src/plugins/hooks.ts` — type re-exports\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts` — embedded harness hook dispatch\n- `src/agents/cli-runner.ts` — CLI harness hook dispatch\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:**\nExtract `tool_use` content blocks from assistant messages and surface them as a structured `toolUses` field in `llm_output` and `agent_end` hook event payloads.\n\n**Real environment tested:**\n- OS: Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64\n- Runtime: v24.3.0, pnpm 8.6.1\n- Setup: OpenClaw local dev instance, real source from openclaw repo\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch:**\n1. Construct an assistant message with mixed content: text blocks + tool_use blocks\n2. Call `extractToolUseBlocksForHook(lastAssistant)` (the new helper added in attempt.ts)\n3. Verify: text-only assistant → empty `toolUses` array\n4. Verify: assistant with tool_use blocks → `toolUses` populated with name + input per block\n5. Verify: `assistantTexts` (text only) and `toolUses` (tools) are complementary signals\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n**Terminal screenshot (reproduction output):**\n\n```\n=== Test 1: Assistant message WITH tool_use blocks ===\nAssistant message has 3 content blocks\nExtracted toolUses: 2 tool-use blocks\n\n  Tool: web_search\n  ID:   toolu_01AbCdEfGhIjKlMnOp\n  Input: {\"query\":\"TypeScript content blocks\",\"max_results\":5}\n\n  Tool: read_file\n  ID:   toolu_02XyZ12345\n  Input: {\"path\":\"/home/user/config.json\",\"encoding\":\"utf8\"}\n\n✅ Test 1 PASSED: tool_use blocks are extracted with name + input\n\n=== Test 2: Assistant message WITHOUT tool_use blocks ===\nExtracted toolUses: 0 tool-use blocks (expected: 0)\n✅ Test 2 PASSED: no tool_use blocks when none present\n\n=== Test 3: assistantTexts (text only) vs toolUses (tools) ===\nassistantTexts (text blocks only): 2 texts\n  \"I'll run a command for you.\"\n  \"Command completed.\"\n\ntoolUses (tool_use blocks only): 2 tools\n  exec: {\"command\":\"ls -la\",\"cwd\":\"/tmp\"}\n  notify: {\"message\":\"Task done\",\"channel\":\"admin\"}\n\nCan supervisor infer tools from text alone? No\nCan supervisor see tools from toolUses? Yes\n✅ Test 3 PASSED: toolUses provides structured tool data that assistantTexts lacks\n\n=== SUMMARY ===\nBefore fix: hook payloads only carried assistantTexts (text blocks)\n           and lastAssistant (raw, untyped). Supervisors had to\n           parse raw message content to discover tool invocations.\n\nAfter fix:  toolUses field explicitly surfaces each tool_use block\n           with name + input, enabling deterministic tool-level\n           policy enforcement from the hook payload.\n\nAll tests passed. ✅\n```\n\n**Test suite output:**\n```\nAll 19 tests passed (6 hooks.correlation + 13 lifecycle-hook-helpers)\n```\n\n**Production change (core extraction logic in attempt.ts):**\n```typescript\nfunction extractToolUseBlocksForHook(\n  lastAssistant: AssistantMessage | undefined,\n): { id: string; name: string; input: unknown }[] {\n  if (!lastAssistant) return [];\n  const content = (lastAssistant as { content?: unknown }).content;\n  if (!Array.isArray(content)) return [];\n  return content\n    .filter((block) => /* type === \"tool_use\" */)\n    .map((block) => ({\n      id: typeof block.id === \"string\" ? block.id : \"\",\n      name: typeof block.name === \"string\" ? block.name : \"\",\n      input: block.input,\n    }));\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n\n**Before fix (broken):**\n```\nllm_output event payload:\n  assistantTexts: [\"I'll run a command for you.\", \"Command completed.\"]\n  toolUses: undefined  ← absent, supervisor can't see tools\n```\n\n**After fix (working):**\n```\nllm_output event payload:\n  assistantTexts: [\"I'll run a command for you.\", \"Command completed.\"]\n  toolUses: [\n    { id: \"toolu_03ExecCmd\", name: \"exec\", input: { command: \"ls -la\", cwd: \"/tmp\" } },\n    { id: \"toolu_04Notify\", name: \"notify\", input: { message: \"Task done\", channel: \"admin\" } },\n  ]\n```\n\n**Summary:** before: supervisors had to parse raw messages or guess from text → after: `toolUses` field provides structured tool invocation data directly in the hook payload.\n\n**What was not tested:** N/A\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- [x] User-facing behavior change? No — additive field, existing fields unchanged\n- [x] Configuration or environment change? No\n- [x] Security or authentication change? No\n- [x] What is the highest-risk area of this change?\n  - Hook event payload shape — plugins reading the type may need to handle the new field\n- [x] How is that risk mitigated?\n  - `toolUses` is an optional field (spread only when non-empty); existing plugins are unaffected\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm test -- --run src/plugins/hooks.correlation.test.ts` passes (6 tests)\n- [x] `pnpm test -- --run src/agents/harness/lifecycle-hook-helpers.test.ts` passes (13 tests)\n- [x] `pnpm tsgo:prod` passes (core + extensions)\n- [x] `pnpm build` passes\n- [x] Change is minimal and targeted (4 files, 81 insertions)\n- [x] No new warnings or regressions\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Next action: waiting for ClawSweeper review\n- What is still waiting: initial automated review\n\n---\n\n*AI-assisted: built with Claude Code*\n",
